.TH "rproc_coredump_add_segment" 9 "rproc_coredump_add_segment" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rproc_coredump_add_segment \- add segment of device memory to coredump
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rproc_coredump_add_segment
.BI "(struct rproc *rproc "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t da "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rproc" 12
handle of a remote processor
.IP "da" 12
device address
.IP "size" 12
size of segment
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add device memory to the list of segments to be included in a coredump for
the remoteproc.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative errno on error.
